1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,894
=Episode 3=
(A Tree Traveling the World)

3
00:01:48,251 --> 00:01:49,251
Hello, Mom. What's up?

4
00:01:49,852 --> 00:01:52,891
Xiaoming, help me find out

5
00:01:54,531 --> 00:01:57,251
the penalty for bigamy
and how to file a lawsuit.

6
00:01:58,772 --> 00:02:01,091
Bigamy? What do you mean?

7
00:02:02,292 --> 00:02:06,331
Who committed bigamy?
That guy surnamed Li?

8
00:02:07,091 --> 00:02:11,532
No, it's just my suspicion.

9
00:02:14,292 --> 00:02:15,812
- Someone's here. You eat.
- Okay.

10
00:02:15,812 --> 00:02:16,451
I'll get it.

11
00:02:18,292 --> 00:02:19,412
Drumsticks are here!

12
00:02:20,252 --> 00:02:21,692
Drumsticks are here! Come on.

13
00:02:22,051 --> 00:02:22,852
Who are you?

14
00:02:23,292 --> 00:02:24,451
- Is Li Wancheng here?
- Who is it?

15
00:02:27,891 --> 00:02:28,451
Oh my god.

16
00:02:36,252 --> 00:02:37,771
Who do you think is at his place?

17
00:02:38,412 --> 00:02:42,532
Mom, why are you always so suspicious?
Do you have paranoia?

18
00:02:42,611 --> 00:02:44,211
How about you see a psychologist?

19
00:02:44,451 --> 00:02:45,451
Watch your tone!

20
00:02:45,651 --> 00:02:46,451
What's with my tone?

21
00:02:47,051 --> 00:02:49,132
You never tell me anything.
What am I to you?

22
00:02:49,611 --> 00:02:51,451
Why do I always
run into unreliable people?

23
00:02:51,812 --> 00:02:52,451
Hanging up now.

24
00:02:56,491 --> 00:02:58,412
(It's not her first time
being unreliable.)

25
00:02:59,532 --> 00:03:00,972
- (Since I was a kid,)
- Ren Xiaoming!

26
00:03:01,252 --> 00:03:02,372
(Qidaohezi, 2004)
(she's been like this.)

27
00:03:02,451 --> 00:03:04,092
Ren Xiaoming!

28
00:03:05,331 --> 00:03:08,171
- What now?
- A whole cartful.

29
00:03:08,211 --> 00:03:09,532
Those three idlers again.

30
00:03:09,532 --> 00:03:10,520
What is all this?

31
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,451
A whole cartload?

32
00:03:12,412 --> 00:03:13,292
Stop looking.

33
00:03:13,292 --> 00:03:14,412
Don't be so stingy.

34
00:03:14,412 --> 00:03:15,132
No.

35
00:03:15,692 --> 00:03:16,412
Just this once.

36
00:03:16,412 --> 00:03:17,651
Can't I just smell it?

37
00:03:18,171 --> 00:03:18,972
Just go.

38
00:03:18,972 --> 00:03:20,252
Just go. Go.

39
00:03:20,252 --> 00:03:21,451
- Go, go.
- So stingy.

40
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,331
Go, go, go.

41
00:03:22,651 --> 00:03:23,608
Come on.

42
00:03:23,608 --> 00:03:24,111
Let's go.

43
00:03:25,491 --> 00:03:26,671
Push it for me. Hurry.

44
00:03:26,891 --> 00:03:28,891
What is this? A huge box?

45
00:03:33,572 --> 00:03:34,532
Mom, what is this?

46
00:03:35,692 --> 00:03:36,192
Don't ask.

47
00:03:36,451 --> 00:03:37,412
What's this stuff?

48
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:40,891
Good stuff. Anyway, our family's about
to turn things around.

49
00:03:41,611 --> 00:03:42,111
Hurry up.

50
00:03:43,372 --> 00:03:45,532
Where did all this stuff come from?

51
00:03:46,651 --> 00:03:49,336
It was supposed to be free benefits
from the hospital,

52
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,412
but no one took them.

53
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,972
They're about to expire,
piled up in the warehouse.

54
00:03:54,931 --> 00:03:57,852
I paid the old warehouse watchman
100 yuan, and he gave me everything.

55
00:03:58,611 --> 00:04:00,891
- Only 100 yuan? For all this?
- Only 100 yuan? For all this?

56
00:04:02,451 --> 00:04:05,931
It's 100 now, but flipping it
will get me way more than that.

57
00:04:06,171 --> 00:04:09,092
Maybe I'll have the capital
to start a small business.

58
00:04:09,451 --> 00:04:11,651
Mom, you'll be a big boss then.

59
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:14,092
Who wants to serve people every day?

60
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:17,368
Eggs become chickens,

61
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:19,172
chickens become geese,

62
00:04:19,612 --> 00:04:20,696
and geese become cows.

63
00:04:21,272 --> 00:04:27,132
Then I will buy an apartment in the city
and a red sedan too.

64
00:04:27,132 --> 00:04:29,651
I'm taking my son and daughter
to travel the world,

65
00:04:29,651 --> 00:04:31,091
going everywhere.

66
00:04:32,091 --> 00:04:33,531
You don't even know how to drive.

67
00:04:35,531 --> 00:04:37,612
It's a dream. My dream.

68
00:04:38,052 --> 00:04:39,612
Not something that happens right away.

69
00:04:39,971 --> 00:04:40,471
Over there.

70
00:04:41,651 --> 00:04:44,372
Where should I do my homework
with all this stuff at home?

71
00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:46,851
You're such a killjoy.
You can write anywhere.

72
00:04:47,252 --> 00:04:47,812
So annoying.

73
00:04:47,971 --> 00:04:50,732
Xiaofei, alright. Come here. Come on.

74
00:04:53,372 --> 00:04:53,932
Get up.

75
00:04:56,572 --> 00:04:58,732
Lie down. Lie down now.

76
00:05:01,091 --> 00:05:03,531
Guard the treasure for me.
Don't let anyone else see it.

77
00:05:03,612 --> 00:05:07,091
- Okay.
- Let's go. Let's go.

78
00:05:17,932 --> 00:05:20,732
Put it here. Here. Here.

79
00:05:20,771 --> 00:05:23,411
This is all full.
Where am I supposed to sleep?

80
00:05:24,372 --> 00:05:25,331
I need the bathroom.

81
00:05:27,211 --> 00:05:29,252
Xiaoming,
what kind of treasure is all this?

82
00:05:30,132 --> 00:05:31,851
Don't open that treasure and look at it.

83
00:05:32,091 --> 00:05:33,692
I'll treat you both
to a good meal later.

84
00:05:34,172 --> 00:05:34,692
Okay.

85
00:05:34,851 --> 00:05:36,211
Let me open it and see.

86
00:05:43,052 --> 00:05:44,052
(Condoms)
What the heck?

87
00:05:45,331 --> 00:05:46,132
So gross.

88
00:05:51,331 --> 00:05:52,492
Why bring everything home?

89
00:05:55,771 --> 00:05:57,771
Why stand here?
Only your brother is working.

90
00:05:58,252 --> 00:05:59,771
I'm making space for you.

91
00:06:24,052 --> 00:06:25,091
So annoying.

92
00:06:57,732 --> 00:07:00,091
Hurry up. Stop singing.

93
00:07:02,372 --> 00:07:04,331
My stomach hurts. Hurry up.

94
00:07:09,211 --> 00:07:13,172
Hurry up. Hurry up.
Mom, what took you so long?

95
00:07:13,651 --> 00:07:15,451
You rush me when I poo
and now when I shower?

96
00:07:15,451 --> 00:07:16,411
You trying to kill me?

97
00:07:59,651 --> 00:08:00,372
What? What?

98
00:08:00,531 --> 00:08:04,012
My homework is all wet!

99
00:08:04,012 --> 00:08:06,492
Hurry up. Come here.
I'll dry it. Let me dry it.

100
00:08:06,492 --> 00:08:08,612
Why did you hang clothes here?

101
00:08:09,971 --> 00:08:12,052
I just finished my homework.

102
00:08:12,612 --> 00:08:13,692
Why is it so wet?

103
00:08:14,012 --> 00:08:14,812
Stop yelling.

104
00:08:14,812 --> 00:08:16,211
Couldn't you see?

105
00:08:16,411 --> 00:08:17,891
- Show me respect.
- Were you blind?

106
00:08:17,891 --> 00:08:18,572
I'll hit you.

107
00:08:18,572 --> 00:08:19,932
This place is a total dump.

108
00:08:20,052 --> 00:08:23,052
People say you collect junk.
Now look at this stuff piled up at home.

109
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:25,304
You don't think.
You pick up and keep everything.

110
00:08:26,531 --> 00:08:27,172
Mom!

111
00:08:27,492 --> 00:08:28,331
I'll hit you!

112
00:08:28,891 --> 00:08:30,211
Mom, stop!

113
00:08:33,411 --> 00:08:33,911
Hitting me?

114
00:08:33,972 --> 00:08:36,571
Every day after school,
I buy groceries, cook, and clean.

115
00:08:36,571 --> 00:08:37,931
I have no place for homework.

116
00:08:37,931 --> 00:08:38,972
What are you doing?

117
00:08:40,051 --> 00:08:41,051
Stop throwing things.

118
00:08:43,051 --> 00:08:46,092
No, you'll break them!
You'll break them!

119
00:08:46,212 --> 00:08:47,092
Okay. Give them to me.

120
00:08:47,092 --> 00:08:47,972
Give them to me.

121
00:08:52,531 --> 00:08:54,372
Next time you curse at me, I'll hit you.

122
00:08:59,092 --> 00:09:01,612
What about my homework?
I just finished it for nothing.

123
00:09:01,811 --> 00:09:04,012
Just rewrite it.
Think of it as extra practice.

124
00:09:09,531 --> 00:09:10,691
Why is it still dripping?

125
00:09:12,332 --> 00:09:13,571
I'll wring it dry for you.

126
00:09:15,252 --> 00:09:15,811
It's my fault.

127
00:09:16,852 --> 00:09:17,691
What's all the water?

128
00:09:22,691 --> 00:09:25,452
The door is blocked.
How am I supposed to get in my room?

129
00:09:26,092 --> 00:09:27,012
Where should I sleep?

130
00:09:28,931 --> 00:09:31,171
Just stack them again.
Think of it as exercise.

131
00:09:45,212 --> 00:09:45,931
Help me out.

132
00:09:47,252 --> 00:09:47,771
Push.

133
00:09:59,372 --> 00:10:03,291
(Compared to dream, I only know
one inadequate substitute word,)

134
00:10:04,092 --> 00:10:04,811
(wish.)

135
00:10:05,531 --> 00:10:07,612
(Wish is practical, straightforward,)

136
00:10:08,252 --> 00:10:08,891
(and small.)

137
00:10:09,612 --> 00:10:12,411
(Like being able to wear new clothes
that fit and belong to me,)

138
00:10:13,171 --> 00:10:14,332
(eating Mom's cooking,)

139
00:10:15,171 --> 00:10:17,171
(or having my own desk to do homework.)

140
00:10:17,972 --> 00:10:19,171
(Do they count as dreams?)

141
00:10:20,051 --> 00:10:22,372
(2023, Qingzhou, Comma)
Xiaoming dreams of traveling the world.

142
00:10:23,372 --> 00:10:27,212
She has an online name:
A Tree Traveling the World.

143
00:10:29,291 --> 00:10:31,612
I specifically brought some photos
this time.

144
00:10:32,012 --> 00:10:34,411
These are all taken by us
around the world.

145
00:10:35,691 --> 00:10:39,171
Since meeting her until now,
we've traveled to 56 countries.

146
00:10:39,811 --> 00:10:42,171
Our passports are full of stamps.

147
00:10:42,411 --> 00:10:46,732
You could say each stamp
paved our path to chasing the dreams.

148
00:10:47,332 --> 00:10:50,651
I'm willing to chase dreams
with her for a lifetime.

149
00:10:51,691 --> 00:10:54,811
Too bad about the 56 countries.
Someone's column stopped updating.

150
00:10:56,092 --> 00:10:57,651
You read my column?

151
00:10:58,012 --> 00:10:59,291
You forgot yourself, didn't you?

152
00:10:59,372 --> 00:11:01,171
Besides being Liu Xiaoran's wife,

153
00:11:01,252 --> 00:11:04,332
you are also a travel blogger
with tens of thousands of followers.

154
00:11:05,012 --> 00:11:06,552
That was so many years ago.

155
00:11:07,608 --> 00:11:08,612
I don't even remember.

156
00:11:10,092 --> 00:11:11,931
A Tree Traveling the World.

157
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:14,411
When you wrote it, I read every issue.

158
00:11:15,171 --> 00:11:17,171
I like that pen name.
Why did you stop writing?

159
00:11:18,531 --> 00:11:21,372
Busy, that's why.
I didn't have time to write.

160
00:11:21,891 --> 00:11:23,811
Busy as a bee, all for someone else.

161
00:11:24,612 --> 00:11:26,732
I was waiting for you
to keep being that tree.

162
00:11:29,012 --> 00:11:31,891
(Actually, traveling the world
wasn't originally my dream.)

163
00:11:32,651 --> 00:11:33,811
(I stole it.)

164
00:11:34,212 --> 00:11:37,012
(2004, Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School)
Class, please close your eyes.

165
00:11:40,732 --> 00:11:44,811
Let's imagine now
that when we are in darkness,

166
00:11:44,972 --> 00:11:47,372
what is the most essential thing
to survive?

167
00:11:48,852 --> 00:11:51,212
No need to raise hands.
Say what comes to mind.

168
00:11:51,651 --> 00:11:52,492
Food.

169
00:11:53,531 --> 00:11:55,651
Food. Anything else?

170
00:11:56,571 --> 00:11:57,171
Water.

171
00:11:57,252 --> 00:11:57,852
Air.

172
00:11:57,911 --> 00:11:58,411
Sleep.

173
00:11:58,411 --> 00:11:59,252
Faith.

174
00:11:59,492 --> 00:12:00,612
Pillow. Blanket.

175
00:12:01,051 --> 00:12:02,852
Yes, sleep is important.

176
00:12:03,651 --> 00:12:07,972
So, let's assume
we have pillows and blankets.

177
00:12:08,372 --> 00:12:10,411
We are in a place where we can sleep.

178
00:12:10,891 --> 00:12:13,811
And we have food, water, and air.

179
00:12:14,612 --> 00:12:19,732
These are the basic elements
all living things need to sustain life.

180
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:23,372
But suppose we're in a dark environment,

181
00:12:23,612 --> 00:12:24,856
just eating and sleeping.

182
00:12:25,528 --> 00:12:27,651
How would you feel?

183
00:12:28,171 --> 00:12:29,252
- Great!
- Great!

184
00:12:29,651 --> 00:12:30,492
Want to die.

185
00:12:35,651 --> 00:12:36,452
What did you say?

186
00:12:46,252 --> 00:12:47,252
Want to die.

187
00:12:49,212 --> 00:12:51,972
Ren Xiaoming, your feeling is sharp.

188
00:12:52,452 --> 00:12:54,492
You can say more about your feeling.

189
00:12:59,051 --> 00:13:02,612
The thought of only eating and sleeping
all day suffocates me.

190
00:13:03,012 --> 00:13:06,171
Plus, seeing nothing,
it's like living in dirty water.

191
00:13:07,051 --> 00:13:09,411
If I had to live like that every day,
I might as well die.

192
00:13:11,651 --> 00:13:15,332
Good. So to survive,
what's the most important thing?

193
00:13:18,811 --> 00:13:19,332
Light.

194
00:13:23,411 --> 00:13:26,051
Yes, even the tiniest bit of light

195
00:13:26,372 --> 00:13:30,012
can awaken the most powerful vitality
in human consciousness.

196
00:13:30,571 --> 00:13:33,411
Where there is light
is where our hearts yearn to be.

197
00:13:34,212 --> 00:13:37,972
As long as there is light,
we won't easily give up our lives.

198
00:13:38,291 --> 00:13:40,732
This light has another name.

199
00:13:42,252 --> 00:13:44,571
(In that moment, she was glowing.)

200
00:13:45,651 --> 00:13:48,452
(And I was the shadow under her light.)

201
00:13:51,811 --> 00:13:53,972
- Dream.
- Dream.

202
00:13:53,972 --> 00:13:56,738
(Dream)

203
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,291
(My Dream)

204
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:04,171
- My dream.
- My dream.

205
00:14:05,492 --> 00:14:06,811
You two, sit down.

206
00:14:09,972 --> 00:14:12,171
Class, I ask you to think.

207
00:14:12,452 --> 00:14:16,811
What is that light in the darkness
that can awaken our life force?

208
00:14:17,291 --> 00:14:19,252
There are many types of dreams.

209
00:14:20,171 --> 00:14:21,411
Some dreams are beliefs.

210
00:14:21,691 --> 00:14:25,732
As you all know, for their dreams,
our revolutionary predecessors

211
00:14:25,852 --> 00:14:27,612
could sacrifice their precious lives.

212
00:14:28,092 --> 00:14:30,171
What about you?

213
00:14:30,651 --> 00:14:33,212
What would you do for your dreams?

214
00:14:33,691 --> 00:14:35,931
And what are your dreams now?

215
00:14:36,452 --> 00:14:39,051
I hope you can seriously think
about it when you get home.

216
00:14:39,372 --> 00:14:42,691
Today's essay topic is My Dream.

217
00:14:42,691 --> 00:14:44,171
(My Dream)

218
00:14:44,171 --> 00:14:46,972
One, two, one, march!

219
00:14:47,171 --> 00:14:49,171
- One, two!
- One, two!

220
00:15:00,492 --> 00:15:01,571
Look at that flag.

221
00:15:02,012 --> 00:15:03,372
Why is Bai Shu so pretty?

222
00:15:03,852 --> 00:15:07,171
Dude, this is the 20th time
you've said that today.

223
00:15:07,492 --> 00:15:08,612
It's because she's pretty.

224
00:15:09,151 --> 00:15:10,571
Xiaoming, tell me, is she pretty?

225
00:15:12,571 --> 00:15:13,092
See?

226
00:15:13,332 --> 00:15:14,212
Everyone says so.

227
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:19,171
(Bai Shu isn't just pretty.
She must have a great dream.)

228
00:15:20,092 --> 00:15:21,012
(What could it be?)

229
00:15:22,811 --> 00:15:23,571
She's so pretty.

230
00:15:27,332 --> 00:15:28,651
What are your dreams?

231
00:15:28,972 --> 00:15:31,051
You mean that essay Ms. Zhou assigned?

232
00:15:34,252 --> 00:15:37,051
How can I write something so personal
like a dream in an essay?

233
00:15:37,492 --> 00:15:39,571
What kind of dream is so private?

234
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,811
My dream? I want to become fireworks.

235
00:15:45,651 --> 00:15:46,372
What?

236
00:15:47,171 --> 00:15:47,972
Fireworks.

237
00:15:49,651 --> 00:15:50,852
Firecrackers and thunderclaps.

238
00:15:50,911 --> 00:15:53,732
Are firecrackers and thunderclaps
even fireworks?

239
00:15:55,332 --> 00:15:57,171
Your essay will definitely get zero.

240
00:15:57,852 --> 00:16:01,411
What's so great about fireworks?
They're gone in a flash.

241
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:04,691
Fireworks are much more expensive.

242
00:16:05,492 --> 00:16:07,252
As a kid, I always watched them
on holidays.

243
00:16:09,171 --> 00:16:11,332
They vanished so quickly,
and I could never get enough.

244
00:16:14,372 --> 00:16:16,492
(We once watched fireworks together
many times.)

245
00:16:17,651 --> 00:16:23,291
(Only years later did I get why
He Yuqiong dreamed of being fireworks.)

246
00:16:25,732 --> 00:16:29,612
Brilliant fireworks,
please keep blooming.

247
00:16:29,771 --> 00:16:31,931
Keep blooming.

248
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,332
Silly goose.

249
00:16:34,171 --> 00:16:38,171
Buddy, come to my place this year.
My dad confiscates tons of it each year.

250
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:41,012
Bai Shu, Bai Shu.

251
00:16:41,252 --> 00:16:43,012
Bai Shu. Bai Shu.

252
00:16:44,171 --> 00:16:45,691
Bai Shu. Bai Shu.

253
00:16:46,012 --> 00:16:47,811
Bai Shu. Bai Shu.

254
00:16:51,771 --> 00:16:52,452
Stop looking.

255
00:16:53,171 --> 00:16:54,612
Why is Bai Shu so pretty?

256
00:16:55,372 --> 00:16:57,092
I think Ren Xiaoming is prettier.

257
00:16:57,531 --> 00:16:58,771
Bai Shu is prettier.

258
00:16:59,531 --> 00:17:01,452
Ren Xiaoming is 100 times prettier
than Bai Shu.

259
00:17:01,452 --> 00:17:03,452
Bai Shu is 1,000 times prettier
than Ren Xiaoming.

260
00:17:04,892 --> 00:17:05,732
You rascal.

261
