that you'd stay in Qidaohezi.

522
00:34:32,852 --> 00:34:35,051
I didn't expect you
to become a cop either.

523
00:34:40,452 --> 00:34:41,852
You're not here to catch up, right?

524
00:34:45,211 --> 00:34:47,096
North American linden
is an introduced species.

525
00:34:47,332 --> 00:34:50,251
Forestry experts say the only patch
is in the Rest Cemetery.

526
00:34:50,611 --> 00:34:51,292
That's right.

527
00:34:51,812 --> 00:34:57,531
Rest Cemetery was established in 1923
by a Canadian missionary, John Peterson.

528
00:34:58,292 --> 00:34:59,531
Maybe it was homesickness.

529
00:34:59,892 --> 00:35:02,680
He brought many linden seeds from home.

530
00:35:04,152 --> 00:35:05,812
He planted them on the back hill.

531
00:35:06,691 --> 00:35:10,091
So how much of this back hill
has those linden trees?

532
00:35:11,932 --> 00:35:13,332
One pops up every so often.

533
00:35:15,051 --> 00:35:16,251
One pops up every so often?

534
00:35:17,091 --> 00:35:21,452
Then when they shed leaves, the hill
must be covered with linden leaves.

535
00:35:22,691 --> 00:35:25,171
Exactly. Every year in October,

536
00:35:25,531 --> 00:35:28,892
once the lindens drop their leaves,
the hill is blanketed with them.

537
00:35:29,812 --> 00:35:30,691
October?

538
00:35:34,412 --> 00:35:37,292
Anything else you need to see?
I have to get off work.

539
00:35:37,691 --> 00:35:38,452
Mom!

540
00:35:40,292 --> 00:35:41,131
My daughter's here.

541
00:35:41,571 --> 00:35:42,452
You're married?

542
00:35:44,211 --> 00:35:44,812
I adopted her.

543
00:35:47,972 --> 00:35:51,251
Her name is Xiaoyu. Yu as in feather.

544
00:35:58,611 --> 00:36:00,691
Mom, are you off work yet?

545
00:36:01,332 --> 00:36:02,211
I'm off work now.

546
00:36:04,772 --> 00:36:05,412
Say hello.

547
00:36:06,251 --> 00:36:08,412
Hello, ma'am and sir.

548
00:36:08,852 --> 00:36:11,571
You must be Xiaoyu. So pretty!

549
00:36:11,731 --> 00:36:13,012
Thank you, ma'am.

550
00:36:14,852 --> 00:36:15,932
And these two are?

551
00:36:16,651 --> 00:36:18,731
- Ma'am, I'm Bai Shu's...
- Li Meng.

552
00:36:20,452 --> 00:36:24,171
Officer Li from Qidaohezi Police's
Criminal Investigation Unit.

553
00:36:24,932 --> 00:36:28,852
Ma'am, I'm Li Meng. I was also
Bai Shu's high school classmate.

554
00:36:29,571 --> 00:36:32,972
I'm Huang Yue, from Qidaohezi Police's
Criminal Investigation Unit too.

555
00:36:34,051 --> 00:36:35,064
Hello.

556
00:36:36,248 --> 00:36:38,852
Are you here to catch up with Bai Shu?

557
00:36:39,171 --> 00:36:41,131
We haven't seen each other
since high school.

558
00:36:41,772 --> 00:36:44,492
They're not here to catch up.
They're here about a case.

559
00:36:46,892 --> 00:36:49,332
What kind of case is it this time?

560
00:36:50,292 --> 00:36:52,812
Ma'am, we can't disclose the details.

561
00:36:54,731 --> 00:36:55,231
Understood.

562
00:36:56,332 --> 00:36:57,651
Xiaoyu, let's go.

563
00:36:57,852 --> 00:36:59,292
Grandma, let's go home.

564
00:36:59,292 --> 00:37:01,012
Okay. Goodbye.

565
00:37:01,012 --> 00:37:01,531
Goodbye.

566
00:37:03,531 --> 00:37:06,492
- Let's go home.
- Let's go.

567
00:37:07,972 --> 00:37:09,051
Are you hungry?

568
00:37:09,372 --> 00:37:10,171
A little.

569
00:37:11,571 --> 00:37:15,492
(Bai Shu was such a sunny,
idealistic girl back then.)

570
00:37:15,852 --> 00:37:18,091
(Now she seems so lifeless.)

571
00:37:18,211 --> 00:37:21,651
Master, the linden trees
don't shed leaves until October.

572
00:37:22,292 --> 00:37:25,492
The statue at Qidian Middle School
was put up during summer break.

573
00:37:25,691 --> 00:37:31,012
How could the dried leaves be found
by a body from three months earlier?

574
00:37:31,131 --> 00:37:32,772
Something's off, right?

575
00:37:34,852 --> 00:37:36,972
(Why is she working
at the Rest Cemetery?)

576
00:37:43,412 --> 00:37:46,372
I heard from your colleagues you like
walking here during lunch breaks.

577
00:37:47,211 --> 00:37:50,731
Chimneys and train tracks always make me
think of the sky and distant places.

578
00:37:51,691 --> 00:37:53,772
Still the artsy type, I see.

579
00:37:54,531 --> 00:37:56,772
Just impractical fantasies, that's all.

580
00:38:01,171 --> 00:38:05,332
I thought someone with your dreams
would have traveled the world by now.

581
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:10,211
By the way, I ran into Ren Xiaoming
at Qidian Middle School the other day.

582
00:38:10,691 --> 00:38:12,440
She said you two haven't talked in ages.

583
00:38:13,452 --> 00:38:16,211
So what? Everyone has their own path.

584
00:38:18,251 --> 00:38:19,051
I don't get it.

585
00:38:20,372 --> 00:38:24,632
Right, Ren Xiaoming's husband
wrote a new book called Breathe.

586
00:38:24,632 --> 00:38:25,332
Do you know it?

587
00:38:25,452 --> 00:38:28,531
I know it. That book plagiarized
my and Ren Xiaoming's diary.

588
00:38:28,651 --> 00:38:31,131
I wondered why the stories
felt like things that happened here.

589
00:38:31,731 --> 00:38:32,731
Tell me about it.

590
00:38:35,731 --> 00:38:36,691
Read it yourself.

591
00:38:41,412 --> 00:38:43,772
Check above the chandelier,
near the AC unit.

592
00:38:43,972 --> 00:38:46,332
Those are prime spots
for hiding cameras.

593
00:38:47,012 --> 00:38:49,812
If you planted a camera on him,
he'd definitely do the same to you.

594
00:38:51,251 --> 00:38:51,812
Got it?

595
00:38:53,452 --> 00:38:56,812
If you find one, video it.
So we have some evidence.

596
00:38:57,171 --> 00:38:59,571
It might come in handy someday.

597
00:39:11,171 --> 00:39:12,892
Liang Yi, I need to go for now.

598
00:39:13,651 --> 00:39:16,372
It's hard to search
while I'm on the phone. My hand hurts.

599
00:39:16,571 --> 00:39:17,772
My hand hurts too.

600
00:39:35,691 --> 00:39:37,091
(Seems he hasn't found it yet.)

601
00:39:51,051 --> 00:39:53,251
(Why would he hide something there?)

602
00:39:54,492 --> 00:39:57,892
(Could he have installed
a camera here too?)

603
00:40:40,664 --> 00:40:41,188
(Wrong password)

604
00:40:43,256 --> 00:40:44,656
(Wrong password)

605
00:41:08,251 --> 00:41:10,412
(Did he hide the diary there?)

606
00:42:31,412 --> 00:42:32,571
(I have a gift for you.)

607
00:42:33,012 --> 00:42:36,251
From now on, don't write your diary
on scrap paper page by page.

608
00:42:37,131 --> 00:42:38,492
Then let's write together.

609
00:42:39,772 --> 00:42:41,372
I'll write my part
and leave it with you.

610
00:42:41,932 --> 00:42:44,012
We have our own diary now.

611
00:42:44,531 --> 00:42:47,332
We can share our secrets in writing.

612
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
